<p>
The <code>SaveType</code> function can be used to save a single <a href="/docs/Types">type</a>.
</p>

<p>
The function takes a single key named <code>Type</code> that must contain a valid <a href="/docs/Types">type</a>.
</p>

<p>
If a field is saved with its <code>"Deprecated"</code> value set to <code>true</code> then it is completely ignored. Deprecated fields are added by comparison with the existing type.
</p>

<div class="heading">Example Request</div>
<pre>
{
    "Type" : {
        "Name" : "Person",
        "Full Name" : "ExampleUser.Person.1",
        "Description" : "A simple person type.",
        "Fields" : [
            {
                "Name" : "First Name",
                "Field Type" : "Text",
                "Required" : true,
                "Array" : false,
                "Description" : "The first name of the person."
            },
            {
                "Name" : "Last Name",
                "Field Type" : "Text",
                "Required" : true,
                "Array" : false,
                "Description" : "The last name of the person."
            },
            {
                "Name" : "Date of Birth",
                "Field Type" : "Date",
                "Required" : true,
                "Array" : false,
                "Description" : "The date of birth of the person."
            }
        ]
    }
}
</pre>